          <h3 class="blog-editorial__title">Pocket Sprung vs Memory Foam: Which Mattress Is Best for You?</h3>
          <p class="blog-editorial__excerpt">Choosing between a pocket sprung mattress and a memory foam mattress is one of the most common questions UK bed buyers face. Pocket sprung mattresses use individually wrapped coils to provide targeted support and excellent airflow — ideal for those who sleep hot or prefer a traditional, responsive feel. Memory foam contours closely to your body shape, eliminating pressure points and reducing motion transfer — perfect for couples and side sleepers. At Klawford, we offer both types in a range of firmness levels from Soft to Extra Firm. Understanding your sleep position, body weight, and temperature preferences is the key to making the right choice.</p>
