          <h3 class="blog-editorial__title">The Complete UK Bed Size Guide — From Single to Super King</h3>
          <p class="blog-editorial__excerpt">Not all bed sizes are equal — and the difference between a King and a Super King could mean the difference between a great night's sleep and a cramped one. In the UK, a Double bed measures 135cm × 190cm, while a King is 150cm × 200cm and a Super King stretches to 180cm × 200cm. If you share a bed, we always recommend going one size larger than you think you need — sleep quality improves dramatically with more space. Our Alexander and Davina collections are available across all UK standard sizes, with our most popular being the King and Super King. Don't forget to measure your bedroom before ordering and check doorway access for delivery.</p>
