          <p class="blog-editorial__date">Sleep Health · Klawford UK</p>
          <h3 class="blog-editorial__title">Best Mattresses for Back Pain Relief — UK Orthopaedic Guide</h3>
          <p class="blog-editorial__excerpt">Back pain affects over 16 million adults in the UK, and your mattress could be making it worse — or better. The right mattress for back pain depends on your sleep position: back sleepers need firm-to-medium support to keep the spine neutral, while side sleepers need softer options to cushion hips and shoulders without letting the spine curve. A pocket sprung orthopaedic mattress provides zoned support that adapts to different areas of the body. Our Klawford Orthopaedic Pocket Sprung Mattress features 1000+ individually nested springs for targeted lumbar support. If you're unsure which firmness is right for your pain level, try our 60-night sleep trial — you can return it if it doesn't improve your sleep within two months.</p>
