        </div>
        <div class="blog-editorial__body">
          <p class="blog-editorial__date">Buying Guide · Klawford UK</p>
          <h3 class="blog-editorial__title">Divan Bed vs Bed Frame — Which Is Right for Your Bedroom?</h3>
          <p class="blog-editorial__excerpt">Divan beds and bed frames each have distinct advantages, and choosing between them comes down to your priorities. Divan beds — upholstered bases on castors — offer an integrated, clean look and often include built-in storage drawers or an ottoman lift, making them perfect for maximising space in smaller UK bedrooms. Bed frames, on the other hand, are statement pieces: the structure of your bedroom's aesthetic. Panel beds, sleigh frames, and wing-back designs all create a focal point that a divan cannot match. At Klawford, we manufacture both — our divan range comes with up to 4 storage drawers or ottoman lift storage, while our luxury frames are available in premium velvets, linens, and leathers. Many customers choose a divan base with a headboard for the best of both worlds.</p>
