          <span class="blog-editorial__tag">Care Guide</span>
        </div>
        <div class="blog-editorial__body">
          <p class="blog-editorial__date">Care Guide · Klawford UK</p>
          <h3 class="blog-editorial__title">How to Care for Your Bed & Mattress — Expert Tips to Make It Last</h3>
          <p class="blog-editorial__excerpt">A quality bed and mattress is a long-term investment, and with the right care, it can provide exceptional sleep for 10 years or more. The single most important habit: rotate your mattress 180° every 3 months for the first year, then twice a year thereafter. This prevents body impressions and ensures even wear. Always use a mattress protector — it guards against moisture, dust mites, and allergens while keeping your mattress feeling fresh. For your bed frame, vacuum the base annually if it's upholstered, and tighten any bolts or fixings every 6 months. Avoid sitting on the edge of the mattress repeatedly in the same spot. Air your mattress monthly by pulling back the bedding for 30 minutes. These simple steps can add years of comfortable sleep to your Klawford mattress.</p>
