<!-- Full-text featured article -->
<div class="blog-featured-article">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="blog-featured-article__inner">
      <div class="blog-featured-article__content">
        <span class="blog-featured-article__label">Featured Guide</span>
        <h2 class="blog-featured-article__title">How to Buy a Bed Online in the UK — The Complete 2025 Guide</h2>
        <p class="blog-featured-article__lead">Buying a bed online in the UK has never been easier — but with so many options, knowing what to look for is essential. This guide covers everything from measuring your room to understanding mattress specifications, so you can shop with confidence.</p>

        <h3>Step 1: Measure Before You Order</h3>
        <p>Before searching for your ideal bed, measure your bedroom carefully. You'll need the room dimensions, doorway widths, and stairwell clearances to ensure delivery is straightforward. As a rule, allow at least 60cm of walkable space on either side of the bed. A Super King (180cm wide) needs a room at least 3.5m wide to feel comfortable.</p>

        <h3>Step 2: Choose Your Bed Type</h3>
        <p>UK shoppers typically choose between <strong>divan beds</strong> (great for storage, clean look), <strong>ottoman beds</strong> (lift-up base for maximum storage), <strong>panel or wing-back frames</strong> (statement aesthetic), and <strong>sleigh beds</strong> (curved headboard and footboard). Consider the style of your bedroom and how much storage you need.</p>

        <h3>Step 3: Select the Right Mattress Firmness</h3>
        <p>Mattress firmness is personal, but general guidance helps: <strong>Soft</strong> suits lighter-weight side sleepers; <strong>Medium</strong> is ideal for combination sleepers; <strong>Firm</strong> suits back sleepers and heavier individuals; <strong>Extra Firm</strong> is recommended for those with lower back pain requiring maximum support.</p>

        <h3>Step 4: Look for UK-Made Quality</h3>
        <p>British-made beds and mattresses are subject to UK fire safety regulations and quality standards. Look for brands that manufacture in the UK, offer transparent spring counts and material specifications, and back their products with genuine guarantees and sleep trials.</p>

        <h3>Step 5: Take Advantage of Sleep Trials</h3>
        <p>Any reputable UK bed retailer should offer a sleep trial on mattresses. At Klawford, our <strong>60-night sleep trial</strong> means you can sleep on your mattress at home — and return it free of charge if you're not completely satisfied. This is far more informative than testing a mattress in a showroom for 5 minutes.</p>

        <a href="/collections/all" class="btn btn--primary" style="margin-top:1.5rem;display:inline-block;">Shop Klawford Beds &amp; Mattresses</a>
      </div>
      <div class="blog-featured-article__img">
        <img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0960/5588/6153/files/pic_2_uphol.webp" alt="buy beds online UK guide Klawford" loading="lazy">
        <div class="blog-featured-article__img-caption">
          <strong>Klawford</strong><br>Handcrafted luxury beds &amp; mattresses, made in the UK.
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

